data.name: L220
data.value: Ipsec Phase12 Policy UNDELIVERED Installation can not be performed due to an abnormal situation. Please check and confirm the following items carefully with the site technician: A. Make sure the device is powered-on and the status LEDs are flashing in orange. B. Check the 2 Data antennas connectors if connected to the correct SMA connectors: Antenna 1 (The Antenna with 2.5mt. cable) must be connected to Port 4G-1 Antenna 2 (The Antenna with 2.5mt. cable) must be connected to Port 4G-2 C. Please check the TIM SIM Card is installed on SIM1 Tray D. Please check the WINDTre SIM Card is installed on SIM2 Tray E. Please check if the RF Status LED in front of the Ricon Router is flashing or fixed F. Please ensure that both antenna cables are untied and there is at least 50cm distance from each antennas. G. Please double check the Ricon Serial number provided by the field technician is correct. H. If all above items are checked and confirmed; ask the field technician to press and hold the reset button on the rear side of the Ricon Router with a tiny tool for at least 20 seconds and release the button after 20 seconds. (The Ricon device must be powered on already while performing this action) I. Please wait at least 2 minutes and confirm the status LEDs on the front side of the Ricon router are flashing continuously. J. Repeat the activation task on RiconApps. K. If the installation returns with an error second time, please contact with your supervisor.
